#. type: Plain text
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:2
msgid ""
"SilverBullet aims to be your workshop for the mind: a creative space where "
"you collect, create and expand your personal knowledge, while also letting "
"you constantly evolve the tools you use to do so."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:4
msgid ""
"While you can use SilverBullet as a simple note taking application that "
"stores notes in plain markdown files on disk, it becomes truly powerful in "
"the hands of more technical power users. By leveraging metadata annotations, "
"its Objects infrastructure, Live Queries and Live Templates, SilverBullet "
"becomes a powerful end-user programming tool, enabling you to quickly "
"develop various types of ad-hoc knowledge applications."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:6
msgid "# Features"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:8
msgid "SilverBullet..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid ""
"Runs in any modern browser (including on mobile) as a PWA in two Client "
"Modes (_online_ and _synced_ mode), where the _synced mode_ enables **100% "
"offline operation**, keeping a copy of content in the browser, syncing back "
"to the server when a network connection is available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid ""
"Provides an enjoyable markdown writing experience with a clean UI, rendering "
"text using Live Preview, further **reducing visual noise** while still "
"providing direct access to the underlying markdown syntax."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid ""
"Supports wiki-style **page linking** using the `[[page link]]` syntax. "
"Incoming links are indexed and appear as “Linked Mentions” at the bottom of "
"the pages linked to thereby providing _bi-directional linking_."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid "Optimized for **keyboard-based operation**:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  - '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid ""
"Quickly navigate between pages using the **page switcher** (triggered with "
"`Cmd-k` on Mac or `Ctrl-k` on Linux and Windows)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  - '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid ""
"Run commands via their keyboard shortcuts or the **command palette** "
"(triggered with `Cmd-/` or `Ctrl-/` on Linux and Windows)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  - '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid "Use Slash Commands to perform common text editing operations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid ""
"Provides a platform for [end-user programming](https://www.inkandswitch.com/"
"end-user-programming/) through its support for Objects, Live Queries and "
"Live Templates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid "Robust extension mechanism using plugs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid ""
"**Self-hosted**: you own your data. All content is stored as plain files in "
"a folder on disk. Back up, sync, edit, publish, script with any additional "
"tools you like."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: src/silverbullet/DESCRIPTION.md:19
msgid ""
"SilverBullet is [open source, MIT licensed](https://github.com/"
"silverbulletmd/silverbullet) software."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/silverbullet/POST_UPGRADE.md:2
msgid ""
"Silverbullet has been successfully upgraded. If you installed some [Plugs]"
"(https://silverbullet.md/Plugs), you'd better update them to avoid "
"incompatibility issues."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/silverbullet/POST_UPGRADE.md:5
msgid ""
"To do so, in Silverbullet, you may either: - open the Command Palette and "
"run: `Plugs: Update`; - or go to the (PLUGS)[__DOMAIN__/PLUGS] page and hit "
"the `Plugs: Update` button;"
msgstr ""
